In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 5-11, 2014, as Fire Prevention Week in the United States. The article emphasizes the importance of taking steps to prevent fires and recognizes the bravery and selflessness of firefighters who risk their lives to fight fires and protect others. The theme for this year's Fire Prevention Week is "Smoke Alarms Save Lives: Test Yours Every Month," highlighting the significance of installing and maintaining smoke alarms. The article also mentions the increasing frequency and intensity of wildfires in a changing climate and encourages Americans to be prepared by developing evacuation plans and clearing flammable vegetation near their homes. Finally, President Obama calls on all Americans to participate in fire prevention programs and activities and to honor fallen firefighters on October 12, 2014.